  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "ACMV Project Manager (Chilled Water Unit)",
  "description": "<ul><li>Lead, manage and coordinate ACMV/Mechanical works for building/industrial construction projects (requires experience in Chilled Water Unit)</li><li>Plan, develop, and manage work schedules to ensure tasks are completed on time.</li><li>Prepare progress reports for clients and project managers, detailing delays, defects, and necessary rectification measures for ACMV/Mechanical-system works.</li><li>Report on progress and arrange site inspections with contractors, subcontractors, and clerk-of-works.</li></ul><p>Requirements</p><ul><li>Minimum 3-5 years of relevant experience with an M&E Contractor in a Managerial capacity</li><li>Diploma/Degree and above in Mechanical, Mechatronics or relevant engineering discipline</li><li>Comfortable with 5.5-Days Workweek</li><li>Advanced knowledge of local code of practice of design implementation.</li></ul><p>If the role resonates with you and your professional experience complements the responsibilities listed, send your resume to <strong>koh.dickson@bayesrecruitment.com</strong></p><p>Dickson KOH, EA Registration R1103367</p><p>bayesrecruitment.com</p>",
